File: Former Nelson Mandela Bay mayor, Mongameli Bobani. JOHANNESBURG - Former Nelson Mandela Bay mayor, Mongameli Bobani has died. Bobani was hospitalised three weeks ago with COVID-19. READ: Outgoing Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu dies aged 54 Bobani was removed as Nelson Mandela Bay mayor in December 2019 through a motion of no confidence. He had been accused of corruption and mismanagement.